reviews: I've bought shakes and smoothies from here before. I recently stopped by after a gym session with my wife and we decided to get some shakes. I got a Green P.B. shake with a scoop of Whey Protein(which was $1 extra) and my wife got the Green Boost.
Ordered delivery:
I wish I could give ten stars, the service was good along with great food - I recommend everyone should try the blueberry lagoon smoothie* omg delicious

I ordered lunch from here several times and my order is always missing something. I even paid for extra items and didn't receive any at all. I always ask for my order repeatedly before hanging up and I'm always disappointed. Never again.

Mmmmm....sandwiches, smoothies, and salads...oh my! Blue Coco is filling the one void the East Harlem lunch scene has had for a while...tasty hot sandwiches. Don't get me wrong, there is some darn good food in East Harlem. But the lunch scene can feel a little redundant at times and lately I've longed for a really tasty panini or hot sandwich. Finally, Blue Coco to the rescue. The sandwiches are the perfect size for lunch and they grill them to just the right temperature to melt cheese, toast bread and avoid any weird singed edges. Call me crazy, but I notice these things! I hate leaving the little leftover burned bites when I want to gobble down a sandwich whole. The Coco Tomping is a customer favorite and I see why. It's not overstuffed, making it easy to eat and savor, and that chicken cutlet was a hefty well seasoned piece. You get a good bang for your buck with this sandwich, I was full for the rest of the afternoon and well into the evening. There's a customer appreciation program for every ten sandwiches bought (I think salads may count too) and you are automatically enrolled on your first purchase, which is great because I always forget all those little punch card things. My coworkers love the salads here as well and I'm looking forward to trying those too. Oh and I gotta try the Morir Sonando smoothie. Only in East Harlem will you find a Morir Sonando smoothie. That's pretty genius I'm definitely going for that next!
Everything is clean. Smoothies are good. Prices are affordable. Great place for a healthy treat.

This is my favorite breakfast, lunch, smoothie, salad, egg & cheese, healthy wrap, food place in East Harlem lol. I love coming here for all the things that were previously listed and I even get large catered breakfast orders (including coffee) from here. The owner is a gem and they are very reliable on the delivery. I order from here EVERY TIME I'm in that area or I have a morning event that needs food. Stop in here whenever you are in the neighborhood and I doubt you will be disappointed.
Great salads. Comes with fresh grilled bread and the lemon dressing was great. This is my new go to salad spot uptown.

Blue CoCo offers the variety and freshness of trendy health foods at a fraction of the price! Tucked away in East Harlem, this gem has quick service, amazing options, and deals galore! With every ten purchases, you can get a small smoothie for free! And if you don't want to make that many purchases? A small (16 oz) smoothie is only $4! My personal fave is the heart healthy one, which includes berries, yogurt, spinach, and flax. And they offer a medium size of 20 oz for only a dollar more - the perfect size in my opinion. I haven't tried their salads, bowls, or açaí bowls, but they are very reasonably priced ($6.50 for a fresh salad in New York?! Unheard of!). Furthermore, they offer discounts if you go in between 3-6 PM! My only gripe is that it closes by 7 PM, so it's a bit difficult to go to for dinner, and it's closed on Sundays. Other than that, wonderful place that shows that it's possible to offer healthy, fresh, affordable food!
Just tried this place for the first time today. Super nice staff. Their acai bowl was delicious and a great price! Will definitely be going back!
Great value, great bagels and Acai!!!
Love this place. I always grab a smoothie before work. Friendly staff, fresh products, and great smoothies/juices.
I came here to grab a bite to eat for lunch on a weekday. It is a pretty small space, so there was not much of a line and I was able to order right away.

I swear by this place ! amazing sandwiches , I love the their  salads and they've helped me transition from a meat eater to a plant based diet . My entire office orders from here and it's great to have healthy choices in the neighborhood. I'm a fan girl !
Custom sandwiches with that small business feel.

This is a great place. I don't like to order out as it can be hit and miss. BUT I have made several orders from Blue CoCo. I don't write reviews, but do read them. So felt I had to write one in this case to alert everyone to this outstanding restaurant. The food is excellent. The drinks the best and the service is beyond good. Usually the food arrives well before the estimated time of arrival. Still VERY hot.
The young ladies working here are very kind. This place is giving residents healthier food choices. I had the morir soñando and the cheeses sandwich.
Could have been better. Overpriced smoothie, coulda made it myself. They charge you extra for everything!!! The Caesar salad isn't too bad, wish I coulda gotten more lettuce for the price.

Love Love Love this place. I just started working in the area so I'm not to familiar with East Harlem. I was looking for healthy food options and to no surprise there aren't many in the area, and then I stumbled across this beautiful gem. The first impression was this is a cute place. The colors of the place gave me an island's vibe. The menu was hand written on the wall, big and clear for everyone to see which I loved. The lady behind the counter was very nice. The salads and green smoothies are fresh!!! I love this place and will continue to come back

Solid 4 stars for this small sandwich salad place. I had the pepperocini sandwich which has salami mozzarella roasted peppers avocado spinach and mayo. The sandwich is constructed properly with thinly sliced avocado that makes the sandwich very stable. No slippin and slidin while taking a bite. Cute place that does smoothies also. Will have to come back to try.

At this price point and at this location (right next to a popular ramen spot), there are high expectations for a japanese restaurant. Having said that, I'm impressed.
Newest Japanese curry place in Hell kitchen! If you've been to other Curry-ya locations, you won't be disappointed. 
This sad amount of pork katsu cost $20... first and last time coming here. Really disappointed.
This place makes me laugh. Their cheapest curry is 9 bucks, and there's NOTHING in there, it's just curry sauce and rice! Are you kidding me?
Fantastic service. Curry was delicious!! Not as spicy as I would've liked it, but still delicious. Would come back! Recommended.
I had the Japanese special curry and it was quite tasty. Five pretty decent sized chunks of beef and very tender. Portions are not as small as some reviews said. I wasn't stuffed after the meal but was satisfied. However it is a little pricey. I wanted to try the baked curry but at $5.5 surcharge it didn't seem worth it. Overall i got my Japanese curry fix, and will be back every now and then
The curry is at most so-so. The serving size did surprise me. I didn't order a kid's meal but it certainly looks and feels like a kid's meal.

Got a tuna subway here two firdays ago and it was pretty good. I have also liked the taste of subway tuna and if I get Subway (which isn't very often) I stick with the tuna. It happened to be that Tuna $6 foot long day so I got a foot long subway. I got lettuce, onion, and tomato on it and It was pretty good.
First off, this location is inside the 875 3rd Ave building and is downstairs in the cafeteria.
Great workers and never any crazy lines.

This Subway is not up to par with any of the other Subways I've frequented.  Twice I've chosen this location over the one right across the street, and both times I was disappointed.  The bread was stale, stale, stale...as I was eating it, it was crumbling in my hand.  Just awful.  My co-worker informed me that she doesn't patronize this particular location for this exact reason.  I got burned twice, and will never go back.  If you're in the area, stick with the one on 52nd Street a few stores West of Third Avenue.  So much better.

They make the best meatball Marinaria sandwiches they have a tibetan guy here who is very friendly. I always get a meatball sandwich and a soup and it always comes out perfect i will always come here they're the best.

Definitely the best Subway around.  The people who work there (presumably a family that owns it, and others) are very nice and extremely efficient.  I go there once a week or every few weeks, and I'm consistently recognized and greeted, and the service is super-quick and accurate.

I needed something quick and thought I'd grab a sandwich from Subway.  Got a 6" BMT.  The quality of the ingredients has gone steadily down the past few years, so I wasn't expecting much; but $5.19 is way over-priced.  Keep it at $4.99 and I wouldn't flinch.  Pass the $5.00 barrier for junk food and I'm through with you.
Mega fast service !

I used to eat at Subway every day for work in high school and then every night when I lived on the UES (I got home late so I wasn't in the mood to make food) and I can honestly say that this place has made the best sub I've ever had at a Subway. The ingredients were unbelievably fresh and an awesome value compared to anything I've gotten around here.

I work in the area and go to Subway pretty often due to the convenience and price.  After finding a bug in one of my sandwiches at the Subway closest to where I work, I had to look for a new place to get my sandwiches.  This is by far and away the best Subway restaurant in the area - consistently quick and friendly service, always stocked with all the ingredients, generous with the toppings, and they have soft and gooey chocolate chip cookies.  If you're looking for a cheap and fast lunch option, this one's a winner!

Now that I work in this building, it is oh so convenient to have a Subways literally 90 seconds away downstairs in the food court!   Especially now that winter's finally here, I dont have to trek out in the horrible weather conditions to get lunch.  With my hectic schedule and little time for lunch, I must come here 2-3 times a week....quality of food is A-OK, service is friendly and fast, and they even introduced me to the Subways card, of which I've gotten 2 free sandwiches in the past 6 weeks.   Thumbs up!
I visited this Subway when I was visiting recently.  Was clean and the food was good.  I recommend the salad with tuna, veggies, and red wine vinegar ... delicious!!

The owner of this place is a nice guy, and quite proud of what he does, and it shows. They do a lot of business, but do it with friendliness and efficiency. As far as the food goes, it's a Subway, very much like any other. It helps to know what you want before you order; I usually let other people get in line in front of me while I decide (I particularly like the wraps and the salad plates; you can have any sandwich as a salad, if you like). The vegetables are always fresh, and they have vegetarian options for those so inclined.
Kudos. The workers here make good sandwiches... the bread is toasted well.. and they actually clean their counter space. Phenomenal :-)  This Subway is downstairs in the atrium of 875 Third Avenue.
This is a very nice place. They always seem to have enough people scheduled during the rushes. Their food and service are always good.

THEY MAKE A MEAN SAMMICH! You go downstairs an office building to the food court area. The sammich prep folks are much more meticulous than the one on 3rd&56st, which spreads your fixins haphazardly like they are in a rush to catch a plane or something. I always get the Roast Chicken, even though it's piecemealed chicken breast, since it's maximum meatage for buckage. You get one breast patty per 6" sub. It's either that or a mystery bbq rib sammich. Definitely ask for your sub to be toasted. It only takes 30 seconds. Now that I can get a footlong for $5, it's a great deal for lunch. This place also honors all Subway coupons so sometimes you can get 2-for-1 footlongs. In addition, you can get two 6" subs for $5 after 5pm here. I  ask for all the fixins (minus jalapenos, raw onion) as that's the only way I'll meet my veggie quota for the day. I always ask for the Southwest sauce and black pepper on top. I know it's bad for you but at least nothing is fried or oily in this sammich. Guessing that footlong is roughly a 750 calorie meal if you drink water. I'm always tempted to fuck with them just for the hell of it and ask for an ABLT or something.

This location is awesome it's very close to my office and the employees are quick. The restaurant is clean and I love walking in smelling the fresh bread. The display is clean and everytime I have ordered I never seen old or bruised vegetables. I highly recommend this location.

Love coming here for their yummy fresh soups! My favorite is the Chicken Pot Pie, Chicken noodle, or Chicken with couscous. All are bursting with some delicious homemade flavors. The staff here is always nice and welcoming and I'm able to get in and out pretty quick. I also enjoy getting a half of the chipotle chicken sandwich which isn't spicey at all but has a nice tangy touch to it. Prices for soups range from $4-11 depending on the type and size you get. Tip: it's best to get a combo with a small soup and half sandwich.
Gave this place so many chances.Never again! A lot of people working here are angry and super rude!!!Don't come here unless you want to be treated like sh****t!!!!

I ordered pickup, and was pretty disappointed. Not many of their soups are that good and they fail at dairy free soups. For 10 dollars I could have gotten a decent meal but at this place I got bad soup, a bad half of a wrap, and an okay thick slice of sourdough.

Good selections of soups. I like to get the soup and sandwich combo when I come here. I have been to this location several times and I have always found it to be clean. The food quality is great and the price isn't too bad.

Its a soup spot plan and simple!!!  Its the fast food of soup joints and its tasty.  HOwever with that said I am not a soup everyday person so when I do go they always seem to have a soup I like.  The service has been freindly and quick no issues except the prices...SMH

NO NOT ORDER FOR PICK UP! Currently eating the most disappointing salad I've had in a while. My salad was not chopped as requested, they completely ignored my special instructions request, and the lettuce is wilted. Just not a good salad at all...

Boggles the mind how this restaurant CHAIN can justify charging $8+ for a CUP of soup that was not even warm when there are plenty of other lunch time eateries in the area. The plus side is that there are 10+ choices daily but good luck finding anything more substantial than broth for under $7!

I had to write a review for this place because I get lunch here all the time when it's cold out... definitely one of the best places in the area! Great selection of soups, and they have a quick grab and go area if you don't want to wait. They're really efficient during the lunch rush and always so friendly!
This is my go to place for lunch.  The staff is always so friendly regardless, how crazy busy it gets.
Came across this quaint little hidden gem walking back to Times Square from Rockefeller Center.  Fantastic soups at a great price!!
Love their ten vegetable soup which is light and filling and perfectly comforting. Yum!

I order online because I didn't have time to wait. I show up 10 minutes after my order was supposed to be ready and it wasn't there. The staff was rude when I asked for my order. They remade my salad, when i asked for a bag I was told I had to go stand in line if I wanted a bag and bread. When I finally was able to eat my salad it was missing half the ingredients.
This place is ok overall. I tried several soups and the second one was very cold, as if the warmer isn't properly keeping the temperature, which of course could be problematic.
I feel like a low of chains get very low reviews, and that's usually because of the staff/service. Well, this location has one of the friendliest faces and best services I have ever seen!
Their Krispy treats are always the best value here, and perfect when they dish out thise random $3 credits for LevelUp campaigns I never participate in after the first transaction.

The service is amazing. the staff are very responsive and make sure that you are satisfied. they are many choices for soup as well. i got the chicken vegetable soup with noodles and it tasted very good although it came out extremely hot so I nearly burnt my tongue. It was very comforting.

The soups are my favorite! My all classic go to soup is the chicken and noodle. I can't forget about the employees. Nathaniel is amazing  very attentive and passionate about his job as an employee! I would rate him 5 stars !
Very sad-looking salad greens and toppings, not to mention UNBELIEVABLY tiny portions for salad toppings!!!

I love Hale & Hearty, and this location is great! The workers are friendly and efficient even though it gets super crowded. I still had to give it four stars because their soups are somewhat over priced, even for the city. They raised their prices a bit last winter and now you can easily pay over $8 for a medium soup alone. I guess there are a lot of Hale & Hearty fans like me so they can charge whatever they want.

I really don't eat salads for lunch, but recently I've been coming by this spot with coworkers. First of all, Hale & Hearty beats Chop't any day of the week. It's cheaper, the lines are shorter, and the staff is generally nice. With that being said, you're still paying upwards of $10 for a salad. This particular location tends to get pretty hectic during lunch hours because of all the nearby businesses. The lines here are split into two: one for salads, and one for soups/sandwiches.
